Depends on PHP 5.4. Under Ubuntu, do:

  $ sudo add-apt-repository ppa:ondrej/php5
  $ sudo apt-get update
  $ sudo apt-get install php5

To load up a WordPress, either:

  $ cd your/wordpress/root/dir
  $ /path/to/wps

Or, from the root of this repo:

  $ ./wps --wp-root=/your/wordpress/root/dir

Then visit http://localhost:8000. WordPress should work normally and you should see lots of output on your terminal.

There are more options. For the full list, do:

  $ ./wps --help 

